Name: Munchausen by proxy
Definition: A factitious disorder that involves a care giver's deliberate exaggeration, fabrication, and/or induce physical, psychological, behavioral, and/or mental health problems in others.

Name: aphasia
Definition: A language disorder that involves an acquired impairment of any laguage modality such as producting or comprehending spoken or written language.

Name: writing disorder
Definition: A learning disability that involves impaired written language ability such as impairments in handwriting, spelling, organization of ideas, and composition.

Name: nosophobia
Definition: A specific phobia that involves an irrational fear of contracting a disease.

Name: autoimmune disease of urogenital tract
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the urogenital tract.

Name: autoimmune disease of blood
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the blood.

Name: autoimmune disease of cardiovascular system
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type II disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the cardiovascular system.

Name: neurological disorder
Definition: A physical disorder that is the result of structural, biochemical or electrical abnormalities in the brain or spinal cord, or in the nerves leading to or from them, can result in symptoms such as paralysis, muscle weakness, poor coordination, loss of sensation, seizures, confusion, pain and altered levels of consciousness.

Name: peripheral neuropathy
Definition: A neuropathy that is located_in nerves of the peripheral nervous system.

Name: popliteal pterygium syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of the face, skin and genitals. Clinical expressions of the disease include cleft lip, with or without cleft palate, contractures of the lower extremities, abnormal external genitalia, syndactyly of fingers and/or toes, and a pyramidal skin fold over the hallux nail. It is caused by mutations in the IRF6 gene located in chromosome 1.

Name: hypersensitivity reaction disease
Definition: An immune system disease that is caused by abnormal immune responses.

Name: lymphoma
Definition: A hematologic cancer that affects lymphocytes that reside in the lymphatic system and in blood-forming organs.

Name: non-Hodgkin lymphoma
Definition: A lymphoma that is characterized as any kind of lymphoma except Hodgkin's lymphoma.

Name: cutaneous T cell lymphoma
Definition: A non-Hodgkin's lymphoma that is caused by a mutation of T cells.

Name: familial juvenile hyperuricemic nephropathy
Definition: A kidney disease that is characterized by hyperuricemia with renal uric acid under-excretion, gout and chronic kidney disease.

Name: Pearson syndrome
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by sideroblastic anemia and exocrine pancreas dysfunction.

Name: marantic endocarditis
Definition: An endocarditis that results from the deposition of small sterile vegetations on valve leaflets.

Name: pre-malignant neoplasm
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body, which do not invade or destroy the surrounding tissue but, given enough time, will transform into a cancer.

Name: benign neoplasm
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.

Name: lymphatic system cancer
Definition: An immune system cancer that is located_in the lymphatic system and is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of lymphoid tissue.

Name: immune system cancer
Definition: An organ system cancer located_in the immune system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation in organs of the immune system.

Name: cell type benign neoplasm
Definition: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the type of cell or tissue from which it is derived.

Name: organ system benign neoplasm
Definition: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the organ system from which it is arising from.

Name: endocrine organ benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.

Name: central nervous system organ benign neoplasm
cardiovascular organ benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm disease located_in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system.

Name: immune system organ benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the immune system organs.

Name: bone benign neoplasm
Definition: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is located_in bone.

Name: sensory organ benign neoplasm
Definition: A nervous system benign neoplasm that is located_in a sensory organ.

Name: thoracic benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplam that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

Name: musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the muscular and skeletal organs.

Name: musculoskeletal system cancer
Definition: An organ system cancer located_in the muscular and skeletal organs and characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the musculoskeletal organs.

Name: benign glioma
Definition: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

Name: central nervous system primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
cerebellar medulloblastoma
Definition: A cerebellum cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

Name: brain glioma
Definition: A brain cancer that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

Name: nervous system benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

Name: sensory system cancer
Definition: A nervous system cancer that is located_in the sensory system.

Name: peritoneal benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the serous membrane lining the abdominal cavity or coelom.

Name: thoracic disease
Definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

Name: pharynx cancer
Definition: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located_in the pharynx.

Name: integumentary system benign neoplasm
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the integumentary system organs.

Name: integumentary system cancer
Definition: An organ system cancer that is located_in the skin, hair and nails.

Name: connective tissue benign neoplasm
Definition: A musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm that is located_in connective tissue.

Name: heavy chain disease
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type IV disease that results from a proliferation of cells producing immunoglobulin heavy chains.

Name: alpha chain disease
Definition: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of alpha antibodies (IgA).

Name: gamma heavy chain disease
Definition: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of gamma antibody (IgG).

Name: mu chain disease
Definition: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of mu antibody (IgM).

Name: delta chain disease
Definition: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of delta antibody (IgD).

Name: akinetopsia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of motion perception.

Name: alexithymia
Definition: An agnosia that is a deficiency in understanding, processing, or describing emotions.

Name: amusia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize musical notes, rhythms, and intervals.

Name: anosognosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to gain feedback about one's own condition or impairments.

Name: apperceptive agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish visual shapes.

Name: apraxia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to map out physical actions in order to repeat them in functional activities.

Name: associative agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize visual scenes or classes of objects but retain the abilty to describe them.

Name: auditory agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguishing environmental and non-verbal auditory cues including difficulty distinguishing speech from non-speech sounds even though hearing is usually normal.

Name: autotopagnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to orient parts of the body.

Name: color agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize a color, while being able to perceive or distinguish it.

Name: cortical deafness
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive any auditory information but whose hearing is intact.

Name: finger agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish the fingers on the hand.

Name: form agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive a whole object while perceiving only parts of details.

Name: integrative agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to integrate these elements together into comprehensible perceptual wholes while recognizing elements of the whole.

Name: mirror agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to acknowledge objects in the neglected field that are visible when a mirror reflects the object visible in the non-neglected field.

Name: pain agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive and process pain.

Name: phonagnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize familiar voices.

Name: semantic agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognise an object while maintaining the use of non-visual sensory systems such as feeling, tapping, smelling, rocking or flicking the object to recognise the object.

Name: simultanagnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recgonize a whole image or scene while retianing the ability to recognize objects or details in their visual field one at a time.

Name: social emotional agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive facial expression, body language and intonation, rendering them unable to non-verbally perceive people's emotions and limiting that aspect of social interaction.

Name: astereognosia
Definition: An agnosia that is the loss of the ability to recognize objects by touch based on its texture, size and weight.

Name: tactile agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize or identify objects by touch alone.

Name: time agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehend the succession and duration of events.

Name: topographical agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to rely on visual cues to guide them directionally due to the inability to recognise objects.

Name: verbal auditory agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognising spoken words as semantically meaningful.

Name: visual agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognize objects.

Name: visual verbal agnosia
Definition: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehending the meaning of written words.

Name: diffuse alopecia areata
Definition: An alopecia areata that involves diffuse loss of hair over the whole scalp.

Name: acquired metabolic disease
Definition: A disease of metabolism that has _material_basis_in enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to an endocrine organ disease, organ malfunction, inadequate intake, dietary deficiency, or malabsorption.

Name: organic acidemia
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder that disrupts normal amino acid metabolism causing a building up of branched-chain amino acids.

Name: survival motor neuron spinal muscular atrophy
Definition: A spinal muscular atrophy that is associated with the survival of motor neuron protein.

Name: Kennedy's disease
Definition: A spinal muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in an X-linked recessive expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine)\nin exon 1 of AR gene encoding the androgen receptor.
Synonym: X-linked Spinal and Bulbar Muscular Atrophy

Name: dentatorubral-pallidoluysian atrophy
Definition: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that has_material_basis_in expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) encoding a polyglutamine tract in the atrophin-1 protein.

Name: body dysmorphic disorder
Definition: A somatoform disorder that involves an excessive concern about and preoccupation with a perceived defect in his or her physical features (body image).

Name: pain disorder
Definition: A somatoform disorder that involves chronic pain in one or more areas, and is thought to be caused by psychological stress.

Name: Kleine-Levin syndrome
Definition: A recurrent hypersomnia that is characterized by recurring periods of excessive amounts of sleep and altered behavior.

Name: bipolar ll disorder
Definition: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one hypomanic episode and at least one major depressive episode; with this disorder, depressive episodes are more frequent and more intense than manic episodes.

Name: seasonal affective disorder
Definition: A mental depression that involves presentation of depressive symptoms only during a specific season of the year.

Name: histidinemia
Definition: A histidine metabolism disease that involves a deficiency of the enzyme histidase.

Name: benign familial infantile epilepsy
Definition: An infancy electroclinical syndrome that is characterized by convulsions, with onset at age 3 to 12 months.

Name: generalized epilepsy with febrile seizures plus
Definition: An idiopathic generalized epilepsy that is characterized by febrile seizures often with accessory afebrile generalized tonic-clonic seizures with childhood onset.

Name: Dravet Syndrome
Definition: An epilepsy that is characterized by frequent febrile seizures with onset before 1 year.

Name: juvenile absence epilepsy
Definition: An adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome statring between the age of ten to 17 years characterized by the occurrence of typical absence seizures.

Name: Timothy syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by cardiac, hand/foot, facial, and neurodevelopmental features. The two forms are type 1 (classic) and type 2, a rare form caused by mutations in a transcript variant of CACNA1C.

Name: GABA aminotransferase deficiency
Definition: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a defect in the gene coding for gamma-aminobutyrate transaminase, which is responsible for catabolism of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), an important, mostly inhibitory neurotransmitter in the central nervous system, into succinic semialdehyde.

Name: succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase deficiency
Definition: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a deficiency of succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase resulting in elevated levels of gamma-hydroxybutyric acid.

Name: gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by impairment of the GABA catabolic pathway.

Name: homocarnosinosis
Definition: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by an excess of homocarnosine in the brain and has_material_basis_in a deficiency of serum carnosinase in its ability to hydrolyze homocarnosine.

Name: familial hemiplegic migraine
Definition: A migraine with aura that is characterized by temporary numbness or weakness, often affecting one side of the body (hemiparesis). Additional features of an aura can include difficulty with speech, confusion, and drowsiness.

Name: Renpenning syndrome
Definition: An intellectual disability that is characterized by small head size (microcephaly), long narrow face, short stature, small testes, and intellectual deficit which follows X-linked inheritance and presents most often in males.

Name: colitis
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease that involves inflammation located_in colon.

Name: ischemic colitis
Definition: A colitis caused_by inadequate blood supply to the colon.

Name: microscopic colitis
Definition: A colitis that can only be diagnosed_by the examination of colon tissue under a microscope.

Name: collagenous colitis
Definition: A colitis characterized by a distinctive thickening of the subepithelial collagen table.

Name: lymphocytic colitis
Definition: A colitis characterized by an accumulation of lymphocytes in the colonic epithelium and connective tissue (lamina propria).

Name: Clostridium difficile colitis
Definition: A colitis characterized by an overgrowth of Clostridium difficile bacteria.

Name: chemical colitis
Definition: A colitis caused_by introduction of various chemicals.

Name: diversion colitis
Definition: A colitis caused_by diversion of the fecal stream due to complication of ileostomy or colostomy.

Name: jejunoileitis
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease that is characterized by patchy areas of inflammation located_in jejunum, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom cramps and has_symptom formation of fistulas.

Name: ileitis
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom abdominal pain, often in the right lower quadrant, has_symptom weight loss.

Name: ileocolitis
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon and located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom abdominal pain in middle or lower right part.

Name: gastroduodenal Crohn's disease
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in stomach and located_in duodenum, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom weight loss and has_symptom loss of appetite.

Name: Crohn's colitis
Definition: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon only, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom rectal bleeding, has_symptom skin lesions and has_symptom formation of ulcers, fistulas and abscesses around the anus.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 1
Definition: The most common type of familial ALS caused_by mutation located_in SOD1 gene located in chromosome 21.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 2
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by mutation located_in alsin gene located_in chromosome 2.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 3
Definition: A type of ALS with loci associated with the disease located_in chromosome 18.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 4
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by mutation located_in senataxin gene (SETX) located_in chromosome 9.
Synonym: distal hereditary motor neuropathy with upper motor neuron signs

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 5
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the spatacsin gene (SPG11) on chromosome 15q21.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 6
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in FUS gene located_in chromosome 16.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 7
Definition: A type of ALS with loci associated with the disease located_in chromosome 20.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 9
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in ANG gene located_in chromosome 14.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 10
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in TARDBP gene located_in chromosome 1.
Synonym: TARDBP-related frontotemporal lobar degeneration with TDP43 inclusions

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 11
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in FIG4 gene located_in chromosome 6.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 12
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in OPTN gene located_in chromosome 10.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 13
Definition: A type of ALS were intermediate-length polyglutamine repeat expansions in the ATXN2 gene located_in chromosome 12 contribute to susceptibility.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 14
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in VCP gene located_in chromosome 9.
Synonym: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, with or without frontotemporal dementia

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 15
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in UBQLN 2 gene located_in X chromosome.
Synonym: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 15, with or without frontotemporal dementia

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 16
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by mutation located_in SIGMAR1 gene (SETX) located_in chromosome 9.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 17
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in CHMP2B gene located_in chromosome 3.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 18
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in PFN1 gene located_in chromosome 17.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 19
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in ERBB4 gene located_in chromosome 2.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 20
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by mutation located_in HNRNPA1 gene located_in chromosome 12.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 21
Definition: A type of ALS with juvenile onset caused_by mutation located_in MATR3 gene located_in chromosome 5.

Name: FTDALS1
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in C9ORF72 gene located_in chromosome 9. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

Name: FTDALS2
Definition: A type of ALS caused_by mutation located_in CHCHD10 gene located_in chromosome 22. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.
Synonym: frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 2

Name: Balo concentric sclerosis
Definition: A demyelinating disease characterized by the fact that the demyelinated tissues form concentric layers.

Name: Cogan syndrome
Definition: An eye disease characterized by nonsyphilitic interstitial keratitis located_in cornea, has_symptom fever, has_symptom fatigue.

Name: Cogan-Reese syndrome
Definition: An eye disease characterized by variable iris atrophy, pigmented and pedunculated nodules located_in iris and attachment of the iris to the cornea (peripheral anterior synechiae) and characterized_by glaucoma.

Name: CREST syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by calcinosis, Raynaud's phenomeno, esophageal dysmotility, sclerodactyly and telangiectasia.

Name: lymph node adenoid cystic carcinoma
Definition: A lymph node cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures of the lymph nodes. These structures are typically filled with a mucous-like material or contain abnormal fibrous membranes.

Name: physical urticaria
Definition: An urticaria induced by external physical influences.

Name: Maffucci syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by the presence of multiple enchondromas (benign growths of cartilage) associated with multiple hemangiomas.

Name: Scheie syndrome
Definition: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by corneal clouding, facial dysmorphism and normal lifespan.

Name: agraphia
Definition: An acquired writing disorder causing a loss in the ability to communicate through writing, either due to some motor dysfunction or the inability to spell.

Name: atrial fibrillation
Definition: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by uncoordinated electrical activity in the heart's upper chambers (the atria), which causes the heartbeat to become fast and irregular and has symptoms palpitations, weakness, fatigue, lightheadedness, dizziness, confusion, shortness of breath and chest pain.

Name: 3MC syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by blepharophimosis, blepharoptosis, highly arched eyebrows hypertelorism, cleft lip and palate, postnatal growth deficiency, cognitive impairment, hearing loss and, in a smaller percentage of cases, craniosynostosis, radioulnar synostosis and genital and vesicorenal anomalies. It encompasses four disorders that were previously designated the Malpuech, Michels, Mingarelli and Carnevale syndromes.

Name: acrofrontofacionasal dysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by intellectual disability, short stature, hypertelorism, broad notched nasal tip, cleft lip palate, postaxial camptobrachypolysyndactyly, fibular hypoplasia and anomalies of foot structure.

Name: Adams-Oliver syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by defects of the scalp (aplasia cutis congenita), abnormalities of the fingers, toes, arms and legs.

Name: intracranial berry aneurysm
Definition: An intracranial aneurysm with a characteristic rounded shape; the most common form of cerebral aneurysm.

Name: Baraitser-Winter syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial features including hypertelorism, large eyelid openings, ptosis, high-arched eyebrows, a broad nasal bridge and tip of the nose, a long space between the nose and the upper lip, full cheeks and a pointed chin; structural abnormalities of the brain might also be present.

Name: basal ganglia calcification
Definition: A basal ganglia disease characterized by the presence of abnormal calcium deposits of unknown cause in the brain; has symptom dementia, psychosis, mood swings and loss of acquired motor skills.

Name: Bruck syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by a combination of multiple joint contractures and osteogenesis imperfecta.
Synonym: osteogenesis imperfecta with congenital joint contractures

Name: branchiootic syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by malformations of the outer, middle and inner ear and branchial and renal malformations. Mutations of the EYA1, SIX1 and SIX5 genes are associated with the syndrome.

Name: cardiofaciocutaneous syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by unusually sparse, brittle, curly hair, macrocephaly, a prominent forehead and bi-temporal narrowing, intellectual disability, failure to thrive, congenital heart defects, short stature and skin abnormalities; it is caused by mutation in the BRAF, MAP2K1, MAP2kK2 and KRAS genes.

Name: Carpenter syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by craniosynostosis, acrocephaly, obesity, syndactyly and polydactyly.

Name: carnitine palmitoyltransferase II deficiency
Definition: A lipid metabolism disorder characterized by an enzymatic defect that prevents long-chain fatty acids from being transported into the mitochondria.
Synonym: lethal neonatal carnitine palmitoyltransferase II deficiency

Name: xanthinuria
Definition: A purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorder characterized by deficiency of xanthine oxidase, resulting in excretion of large amounts of xanthine in the urine and the formation of xanthine stones.

Name: Warburg micro syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by severe intellectual disability, microcephaly, congenital cataract, microcornea, microphthalmia, agenesis or hypoplasia of the corpus callosum and hypogenitalism.

Name: Van Maldergem syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by facial abnormalities such as telecanthus, epicanthus, broad flattened nose, large inverted W-shaped mouth and malformed ears, malformed extremities such as camptodactyly, clinodactyly, interdigital webbing and joint hyperlaxity and mental retardation.

Name: Van der Woude syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by the combination of lower lip pits, cleft lip with or without cleft palate and cleft palate alone.

Name: UV-sensitive syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by photosensitivity and liver spots (solar lentigines).

Name: 3-M syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by dwarfism, facial dysmorphia and skeletal abnormalities.

Name: synpolydactyly
Definition: A syndactyly characterized by an increased number of digits; often a result of a mutation in the HOX D13 gene.

Name: stuttering
Definition: An articulation disorder characterized by involuntary sound repetition and disruption or blocking of speech.

Name: specific language impairment
Definition: A language disorder characterized by difficulty in language acquisition despite otherwise normal development and in the absence of any obvious explanatory factors.

Name: Mast syndrome
Definition: A hereditary spastic paraplegia associated with dementia.

Name: MASA syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by hydrocephalus, spasticity of the lower limbs, adducted thumbs, aphasia, seizures, agenesis of the corpus callosum and intellectual disability in the mild to moderate range.

Name: Smith-McCort dysplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia characterized by short limbs and a short trunk with a barrel-shaped chest and caused_by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DYM gene on chromosome 18q.

Name: Simpson-Golabi-Behmel syndrome
Definition: An X-linked disease characterized by pre- and postnatal overgrowth and craniofacial, skeletal, cardiac and renal abnormalities.

Name: scoliosis
Definition: A bone structure disease characterized by an appreciable lateral deviation in the normally straight vertical line of the spine.

Name: idiopathic scoliosis
Definition: A scoliosis with no known cause.

Name: sclerosteosis
Definition: A hyperostosis characterized by excessive bone formation most prominent in the skull, mandible, clavicle, ribs and diaphyses of long bones; bone formation occurs throughout life.

Name: sclerocornea
Definition: A corneal disease in which the cornea blends with sclera, resulting in clouding of the cornea.

Name: scapuloperoneal myopathy
Definition: A muscular dystrophy which begins at the lower legs and affects the shoulder region earlier and more severely than distal arm.

Name: Robinow syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by mild to moderate short stature due to growth delays after birth, distinctive craniofacial abnormalities, skeletal malformations and genital abnormalities.

Name: rippling muscle disease
Definition: A muscle tissue disease characterized by muscles unusually sensitive to movement or pressure; the proximal muscles are most affected, especially the thighs.

Name: Dowling-Degos disease
Definition: A pigmentation disease characterized by a reticulate pattern of abnormally dark skin coloring, particularly in the body's folds and creases.

Name: dyschromatosis symmetrica hereditaria
Definition: A pigmentation disease characterized by progressively pigmented and depigmented macules, often mixed in a reticulate pattern, concentrated on the dorsal extremities.

Name: reticulate acropigmentation of Kitamura
Definition: A pigmentation disease characterized by lesions that initially arise as letiginous, hyperpigmented macules in a reticular pattern on the dorsal aspect of the hands and feet. Over time, lesions may spread proximally and may darken; palmoplantar pitting and dermatoglyphic disruption may also be present.

Name: renal-hepatic-pancreatic dysplasia
Definition: A physical disorder characterized by pancreatic fibrosis, renal dysplasia and hepatic dysgenesis; it is usual fatal soon after birth.

Name: ptosis
Definition: An eye disease characterized by the drooping or falling of the upper or lower eyelid.

Name: congenital ptosis
Definition: A ptosis characterized by eyelid drop present at birth.

Name: gallbladder disease
Definition: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the gallbladder.

Name: primary pigmented nodular adrenocortical disease
Definition: An adrenal cortex disease characterized by small to normal sized adrenal glands containing multiple small cortical pigmented nodules.

Name: photosensitive epilepsy
Definition: An epilepsy characterized by seizures triggered by visual stimuli that form patterns in space or time, such as flashing lights.

Name: Ohdo syndrome
Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, dental hypoplasia, hearing impairment and intellectual disability.

Name: oculodentodigital dysplasia
Definition: A syndrome characterized by craniofacial, neurologic, limb and ocular abnormalities.

Name: cold-induced sweating syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by problems with regulating body temperature and other abnormalities affecting many parts of the body; caused_by mutations in the CRLF1 gene.

Name: congenital secretory chloride diarrhea 1
Definition: A secretory diarrhea caused_by mutation in the SLC26A3 gene.

Name: dyschromatosis universalis hereditaria
Definition: A pigmentation disease characterized by reticulate hyper- and hypo-pigmentated macules in a generalized distribution.

Name: megalocornea
Definition: A corneal disease characterized by a bilaterally enlarged corneal diameter without an increase in intraocular pressure; caused_by mutation in the CHRDL1 gene.

Name: Meier-Gorlin syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disorder characterized by severe intrauterine and postnatal growth retardation, microcephaly, bilateral microtia and hypoplastic patellae.

Name: autosomal dominant non-syndromic intellectual disability
Definition: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

Name: autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability
Definition: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

Name: syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
Definition: A syndromic intellectual characterized by an X-linked inheritance pattern.

Name: uvulitis
Definition: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the swelling of the uvula to 3-5 times its normal size.

Name: adenoid hypertrophy
Definition: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the unusual growth of the adenoid tonsil; has_symptom snoring, has_symptom hyponasality, has_symptom otitis media with effusion, has symptom mouth breathing.

Name: angular cheilitis
Definition: A cheilitis characterized by inflammation of one or both of the corners of the mouth.

Name: tracheomalacia
Definition: A tracheal disease characterized by flaccidity of the tracheal support cartilage.

Name: persistent generalized lymphadenopathy
Definition: A lymph node disease characterized by enlarged, non-painful lymph nodes occurring for more than three to six months for which no other reason can be found.

Name: oral hairy leukoplakia
Definition: A mouth disease characterized by a white patch on the side of the tongue with a corrugated or hairy appearance; caused by Epstein-Barr virus.

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome I
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome characterized_by polycystic kidney disease and variable involvement of the central nervous system and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance of the OFD1 gene.

Name: lung abscess
Definition: A lung disease characterized by microbial infection which causes a type of liquefactive necrosis of the pulmonary tissue and formation of cavities containing necrotic debris or fluid.

Name: acute promyelocytic leukemia
Definition: An acute myeloid leukemia characterized by accumulation of promyelocytes in the bone marrow and by a translocation between chromosomes 15 and 17.

Name: cardiac arrest
Definition: A congestive heart failure characterized by a sudden stop in effective blood circulation due to the failure of the heart to contract effectively or at all.

Name: inguinal hernia
Definition: An intestinal disease characterized by a protrusion of abdominal cavity contests through the inguinal canal.

Name: umbilical hernia
Definition: A intestinal disease characterized by the protrusion by part of the intestine though an opening in the abdominal muscles.

Name: mastoiditis
Definition: A middle ear disease characterized by an inflammation of the mucosal lining of the mastoid antrum and the mastoid air cell system inside the mastoid process.

Name: breast abscess
Definition: A breast disease characterized by a collection of pus in the breast.

Name: dental abscess
Definition: A tooth disease characterized by a localized collection of pus associated with a tooth.

Name: cervical polyp
Definition: A cervix disease characterized by a benign polyp on the surface of the cervical canal.

Name: myelomeningocele
Definition: A spina bifida characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord through an opening, covered by meningeal membranes.

Name: omphalocele
Definition: A physical disorder characterized by a defect in the development of the abdominal wall muscles, resulting in the intestines, liver and other organs to remain outside of the abdomen in a sac.

Name: anal fistula
Definition: An anus disease characterized by is an abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin.

Name: ectopic pregnancy
Definition: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the implantation of the embryo outside the uterine cavity.

Name: Rapp-Hodgkin syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of ectodermal tissues including the skin, hair, nails, teeth and sweat glands and anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with cleft lip/palate.
Synonym: anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with cleft lip/palate

Name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 2
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the TMEM70 gene on chromosome 8q21.
Synonym: neonatal mitochondrial encephalocardiomyopathy due to ATP synthase deficiency

Name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 3
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the ATP5E gene on chromosome 20q13.

Name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 4
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has material basis in mutation in the ATP5A1 gene on chromosome 18q.

Name: transient neonatal diabetes mellitus
Definition: A neonatal diabetes mellitus characterized by hyperglycemia during the neonatal period that remits during infancy but recurs in later life in most patients.

Name: autosomal dominant sideroblastic anemia
Definition: A sideroblastic anemia characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

Name: CEDNIK syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease caused by homozygous mutation the SNAP29 gene and characterized by a unique constellation of clinical manifestations including microcephaly, severe neurologic impairment, psychomotor retardation, failure to thrive, facial dysmoprhism, palmoplantar keratoderma and late-onset ichthyosis.
Synonym: cerebral dysgenesis, neuropathy, ichthyosis and keratoderma syndrome

Name: parameningeal embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: An embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma located in the parameningeal region.

Name: chronic atrial and intestinal dysrhythmia
Definition: A syndrome characterized by a unique combination of cardiac arrhythmias and intestinal pseudo-obstruction; caused by the mutated SGOL1 protein. Distinctive clinical features include atrial dysrhythmias, sick sinus syndrome (SSS) and valve anomalies and chronic intestinal pseudo-obstruction (CIPO).

Name: ciliopathy
Definition: A genetic disease associated with mutations encoding defective proteins, which result in either abnormal function formation or function of cilia.

Name: agnathia-otocephaly complex
Definition: A physical disorder characterized by mandibular hypoplasia or agnathia, ventromedial auricular malposition (melotia) and/or auricular fusion (synotia), and microstomia with oroglossal hypoplasia or aglossia. Holoprosencephaly is the most commonly identified association, but skeletal, genitourinary and cardiovascular anomalies and situs inversus have been reported.

Name: acromelic frontonasal dysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by cranium bifidum, severe hypertelorism, median cleft lip and palate, nasal bifurcation, brachycephaly, large fontanelle, tibial hemimelia, preaxial polydactyly of the feet and brain malformations.

Name: glucocorticoid-induced osteoporosis
Definition: An osteoporosis caused by chronic glucocorticoid use. Glucocorticoids impair the replication, differentiation and function of osteoblasts and induce the apoptosis of mature osteoblasts and osteocytes; the also favor osteoclastogenesis leading to an increase in bone resorption.

Name: acrodermatitis chronica atrophicans
Definition: An acrodermatitis characterized by a chronically progressive course, leading to widespread atrophy of the skin. It is a clinical manifestation of Lyme borreliosis.

Name: bacillary angiomatosis
Definition: A bartonellosis that has_material_basis_in Bartonella henselae or has_material_basis_in Bartonella quintana. The disease is characterized by the proliferation of blood vessels, resulting in them forming tumour-like masses in the skin and other organs.

Name: Native American myopathy
Definition: A neuromuscular disease characterized by congenital weakness, arthrogryposis, cleft palate, ptosis, myopathic facies, short stature, kykphoscoliosis, talipes deformities and susceptibility to malignant hyperthermia provoked by anesthesia; caused by homozygous mutation in the STAC3 gene on chromosome 12q13.

Name: acrorenal syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by limb defects, usually bilateral, like cleft hands or feet and longitudinal defects involving radius or ulna, tibia or fibula and renal anomalies which include agenesis, hypoplasia and rarely polycystic kidneys. Additional malformations may involve the oro-mandibular region, the trachea and lungs, skin derivatives including sweat glands, mammary glands, the uterus, vas deferens, the nasal placodes and the eyes.

Name: hypoparathyroidism-retardation-dysmorphism syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by permanent parathyroid hormone (PTH) deficiency, hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia, facial anomalies, and psychomotor retardation; it is seen among children born to consanguineous couple of Arab ethnicity.

Name: microcephaly with or without chorioretinopathy, lymphedema, or mental retardation
Definition: A syndrome characterized byvariable expression of microcephaly, ocular disorders including chorioretinopathy, congenital lymphedema of the lower limbs, and mild to moderate intellectual disability.

Name: adenine phosphoribosyltransferase deficiency
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by the formation 2,8-dihydroxyadenine stones and renal failure secondary to intratubular crystalline precipitation. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 2
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease characterized by motor disability, with ataxia, apraxia, dystonia, and dysarthria, associated with necrotic lesions throughout the brain and has material basis in mutation in the TTC19 gene on chromosome 17. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

Name: Kleefstra syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by childhood hypotonia, a distinctive facial appearance, speech impediments and developmental disability, as well as epilepsy, congenital and urogenetic defects, microcephaly, corpulence, and psychiatric disorders. It is caused either by a microdeletion in the chromosome region 9q34.3 or by a point mutation in the EHMT1 gene located in that region.

Name: acrofacial dysostosis Cincinnati type
Definition: An acrofacial dysostosis characterized by a spectrum of mandibulofacial dysostosis phenotypes, such as cleft palate, micrognathia, malar flattening, microcephaly and, in some cases, extrafacial skeletal defects. It is caused by heterozygous mutation in the POLR1A gene located in chromosome 2p11.

Name: Stormorken syndrome
Definition: A blood platelet disease characterized by thrombocytopathy, thrombocytopenia, mild anemia, asplenia, tubular aggregate myopathy, miosis, headache, and ichthyosis. It is caused by heterozygous in the STM1 gene located in chromosome 11p15. It has an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

Name: amyotrohpic lateral sclerosis type 22
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis caused_by mutation located_in TUBA4A gene located_in chromosome 2q35.

Name: Vici syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by callosal agenesis, cataracts, cardiomyopathy, combined\nimmunodeficiency and hypopigmentation. It is caused by mutation in the EPG5 gene located in chromosome 18q12.3.
Synonym: immunodeficiency with cleft lip/palate, cataract, hypopigmentation, and absent corpus callosum

Name: chylomicron retention disease
Definition: A lipid metabolism disorder characterized by malnutrition, failure to thrive, growth failure, vitamin E deficiency and the absence of chylomicrons and apolipoprotein B48 post-prandially. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern and is caused by mutations in the SAR1B gene located in chromosome 5q31.1.

Name: multiple acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency
Definition: An inherited metabolic disorder characterized by the body's inability to break down proteins and fats to produce energy. It is a disorder of fatty acid,amino acid, and choline metabolism and has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern. It is caused by mutations in the ETFA, ETFB and ETFDH genes. It presents three clinical phenotypes: a neonatal-onset form with congenital anomalies (type I), a neonatal-onset form without congenital anomalies (type II), and a late-onset form (type III). The neonatal-onset forms are usually fatal.

Name: Sakati-Nyhan syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by abnormalities in the bones of the legs, congenital heart defects and craniofacial defects and craniosynostosis. The patients suffer from cyanosis and other respiratory and breathing infections.

Name: hereditary papulotranslucent acrokeratoderma
Definition: A keratosis of the hands and feet characterized by persistent, asymptomatic, yellowish to white papules and plaques associated with fine-textured scalp hair and an atopic diathesis.

Name: punctate palmoplantar keratoderma
Definition: A palmoplantar keratosis characterized by keratoses with a \raindrop\" pattern on the palmoplantar surface, skin lesions which may involve the whole of the palmoplantar surface, or may be more restricted in their distribution."

Name: glycerol kinase deficiency
Definition: An inherited metabolic disorder characterized_by wide range of phenotypic variability; patients can have severe metabolic and CNS abnormalities, while others possess hyperglycerolemia and glyceroluria with no other apparent phenotype. It is caused by mutation in the GK gene on chromosome Xp21.

Name: Galloway-Mowat syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized_by is a rare autosomal recessive disease, characterized by microcephaly with brain anomalies including CA in some cases, intellectual disability, and early-infantile-onset nephrotic syndrome.

Name: mandibulofacial dysostosis with alopecia
Definition: A syndrome characterized_by malar and mandibular hypoplasia, typically associated with abnormalities of the ears and eyelids, and with alopecia.

Name: Hennekam syndrome
Definition: A lymphatic system disease characterized by he presence of intestinal lymphangiectasia, mental retardation, and characteristic facial anomalies. It in inherited in an autosomal recessive pattern. Most individuals with Hennekam syndrome have characteristic facial abnormalities, such as a flat face with accompanying puffy eyelids and hypertelorism; the nasal bridge is typically flat and the ears are typically small. Congenital extremity and genital lymphedema is present in most patients.

Name: autosomal dominant Parkinson disease 1
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by mutation in the alpha-synuclein gene, SNCA, on chromosome 4q22.1.

Name: autosomal recessive juvenile Parkinson disease 2
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by mutation in the parkin gene, PARK2, on chromosome 6q25.2-q27.

Name: early-onset Parkinson disease 6
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by mutations in the PINK1 gene located on chromosome 1p36.12.

Name: autosomal recessive early-onset Parkinson disease 7
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DJ1 gene on chromosome 1p36.

Name: autosomal dominant Parkinson disease 8
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by heterozygous mutation in the gene encoding dardarin , LRRK2, located on chromosome 12q12.

Name: autosomal recessive early-onset Parkinson disease 15
Definition: A Parkinson's disease caused by mutation in the FBXO7 gene located on chromosome 22q12.3.

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome V
Synonym: polydactyly, postaxial, with median cleft of upper lip

Name: Joubert syndrome with orofaciodigital defect
Definition: A Joubert syndrome subtype with orofaciodigital defect.

Name: Cole-Carpenter syndrome
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta characterized by craniosynostosis, communicating hydrocephalus, ocular proptosis, marked postnatal growth failure, and distinctive facial appearance.

Name: lysinuric protein intolerance
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by the body's inability to effectively break down lysine, arginine and ornithine and by renal hyperdiaminoaciduria, especially lysinuria, and by impaired formation of urea with hyperammonemia after protein ingestion. It is caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the amino acid transporter gene SLC7A7 on chromosome 14q11.

Name: Desbuquois dysplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia characterized by short stature, joint laxity, scoliosis, and advanced carpal ossification with a delta phalanx.
Synonym: micromelic dwarfism with vertebral and metaphyseal abnormalities and advanced carpotarsal ossification

Name: NUT midline carcinoma
Definition: A carcinoma that is characterized by a BRD4-NUT translocation involving the rearrangement of the bromodomain-containing protein 4 (BRD4) and the gene encoding nuclear protein of the testis (NUT) at 15q14, BRD4-NUT t(15;19)(q14;q13.1) and arises from midline epithelial structures, most commonly the head, neck, and mediastinum.
Synonym: nuclear protein in testis midline carcinoma

Name: Feingold syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by variable combinations of microcephaly, limb malformations, esophageal and duodenal atresias, and learning disability/mental retardation.

Name: gingival fibromatosis
Definition: A gingival overgrowth characterized by benign, slowly progressive, nonhemorrhagic, fibrous enlargement of the oral masticatory mucosa.

Name: Holt-Oram syndrome
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by congenital anomalies located_in heart and located_in upper limb.

Name: Miller-Dieker lissencephaly syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by classical lissencephaly and distinct facial features. Visible and submicroscopic deletions of 17p13.3, including the LIS1 gene, are found in almost 100% of patients.

Name: salt and pepper syndrome
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by severe intellectual disability, epilepsy, scoliosis, choreoathetosis, dysmorphic facial features and altered dermal pigmentation.

Name: fetal valproate syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial appearance, a cluster of minor and major anomalies and central nervous system dysfunction.

Name: Kindler syndrome
Definition: A skin disease characterized by congenital blistering, skin atrophy, photosensitivity, skin fragility, and scaling.

Name: Kabuki syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by multiple congenital anomalies and mental retardation. Other characteristics include a peculiar facial gestalt, short stature, skeletal and visceral abnormalities, cardiac anomalies, and immunological defects.

Name: childhood onset epileptic encephalopathy
Definition: An idiopathic generalized epilepsy characterized by onset of multiple seizure types in the first few years of life and associated with poor prognosis. Affected individuals have cognitive regression and intellectual disability.

Name: Perlman syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by polyhydramnios with neonatal macrosomia, nephromegaly, distinctive facial appearance, renal dysplasia, nephroblastomatosis, and predisposition to Wilms tumor. It shows similarities to Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome.
Synonym: renal hamartomas, nephroblastomatosis and fetal gigantism

Name: Zika fever
Definition: A viral infectious disease that has_material_basis in Zika virus, which is transmitted_by Aedes aegypti mosquitoes.

Name: Shwachman-Diamond syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by exocrine pancreatic insufficiency, bone marrow failure and skeletal abnormalities.

Name: left ventricular noncompaction
Definition: An intrinsic cardiomyopathy characterized by distinctive (spongy) morphological appearance of the LV myocardium.

Name: Goldberg-Shprintzen syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by intellectual disability, specific facial gestalt and Hirschsprung's disease (HSCR). It is caused by homozygous mutation in the KIAA1279 gene on chromosome 10q21.1.

Name: oculoauricular syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by microcornea, microphthalmia, anterior-segment dysgenesis, cataract, coloboma of various parts of the eye, abnormalities of the retinal pigment epithelium, and rod-cone dystrophy and a particular cleft ear lobule.

Name: MEDNIK syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by mental retardation, enteropathy, deafness, peripheral neuropathy, ichthyosis, and keratoderma. It is cause by homozygous mutation in the AP1S1 gene on chromosome 7q22.
Synonym: mental retardation, enteropathy, deafness, neuropathy, ichthyosis, keratodermia

Name: EAST syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterize by seizures, sensorineural deafness, ataxia, mental retardation, and electrolyte imbalance. It is caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the KCNJ10 gene on chromosome 1q23.

Name: Mowat-Wilson syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by a distinct facial phenotype (high forehead, frontal bossing, large eyebrows, medially flaring and sparse in the middle part, hypertelorism, deep set but large eyes, large and uplifted ear lobes, with a central depression, saddle nose with prominent rounded nasal tip, prominent columella, open mouth, with M-shaped upper lip, frequent smiling, and a prominent but narrow and triangular pointed chin), moderate-to-severe intellectual deficiency, epilepsy and variable congenital malformations including Hirschsprung disease, genitourinary anomalies (in particular hypospadias in males), congenital heart defects, agenesis of the corpus callosum and eye anomalies. It is caused by de novo heterozygous mutation in the ZEB2 gene on chromosome 2q22.
Synonym: microcephaly, mental retardation, and distinct facial featrues, with or without Hirschprung disease

Name: Perry syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by parkinsonism, hypoventilation, depression, and weight loss; caused by heterozygous mutation in the DCTN1 gene on chromosome 2p13.. The mean age at onset is 48 years; the mean disease duration is five years. Parkinsonism and psychiatric changes (depression, apathy, character changes, and withdrawal) tend to occur early; severe weight loss and hypoventilation manifest later.
Synonym: parkinsonism with alveolar hypoventilation and mental depression

Name: Pitt-Hopkins syndrome
Definition: A syndrome characterized by intellectual disability and developmental delay, breathing problems, recurrent seizures (epilepsy), and distinctive facial features. It is caused by heterozygous de novo mutations in the TCF4 gene in chromosome 18q21.

Name: Schimke immuno-osseous dysplasia
Definition: A spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia characterized by short stature with hyperpigmented macules and an unusual facies, proteinuria with progressive renal failure, lymphopenia with recurrent infections, and cerebral ischaemia. It is caused by mutations in the SMARCAL1 gene.

Name: SPOAN syndrome
Definition: A neurodegenerative disease characterized by spastic paraplegia, axonal neuropathy, dysarthria, acoustic startle, and congenital optical atrophy. It is caused by homozygous mutation in the KLC2 gene on chromosome 11q13.2.
Synonym: spastic paraplegia, optic atropy, and neuropathy syndrome

Name: chicken egg allergy
Definition: An egg allergy triggered by Gallus gallus eggs.

Name: shellfish allergy
Definition: A food allergy triggered by Crustacea or Mollusca.

Name: respiratory allergy
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease located in the respiratory tract.

Name: pollen allergy
Definition: A respiratory allergy triggered by pollen.

Name: Timothy grass allergy
Definition: A pollen allergy triggered by Phleum pratense pollen.

Name: autoimmune neuropathy
Definition: An autoimmune disease of centreal nervous system caused by an autoimmune response.

Name: drug allergy
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by a drug.

Name: metal allergy
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by a metal.

Name: gastrointestinal allergy
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease located in the gastrointestinal tract.

Definition: A food allergy triggered by a plant fruit product.

Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Malus domestica plant fruit food product.

Name: apricot allergy
Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus armeniaca plant fruit food product.

Name: cherry allergy
Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus avium plant fruit food product.

Name: Indian plum allergy
Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Ziziphus mauritiana plant fruit food product.

Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Citrus sinensis plant fruit food product.

Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Cucumis melo plant fruit food product.

Name: peach allergy
Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus persica plant fruit food product.

Name: plum allergy
Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus domestica plant fruit food product.

Definition: A fruit allergy triggered by Solanum lycopersicum plant fruit food product.

Definition: A food allergy triggered by fish.

Definition: A fish allergy triggered by Gadus morhua.

Definition: A fish allergy triggered by Salmo salar.

Definition: A fish allergy triggered by Cyprinus carpio.

Definition: A fish allergy triggered by Danio rerio.

Definition: A fish allergy triggered by Oncorhynchus mykiss.

Definition: A drug allergy triggered by a beta-lactam (-lactam).

Definition: A beta-lactam allergy triggered by penicillin.

Name: cow milk allergy
Definition: A milk allergy triggered by Bos taurus milk.

Name: goat milk allergy
Definition: A milk allergy triggered by Capra hircus milk.

Name: mollusc allergy
Definition: A shellfish allergy triggered by Mollusca.

Name: crustacean allergy
Definition: A shellfish allergy triggered by Crustacea.

Name: brown shrimp allergy
Definition: A crustacean allergy triggered by Farfantepenaeus aztecus.

Definition: A crustacean allergy triggered by Scylla paramamosain.

Definition: A crustacean allergy triggered by Fenneropenaeus indicus.

Definition: A crustacean allergy triggered by Penaeus monodon.

Definition: A crustacean allergy triggered by Litopenaeus vannamei.

Name: snail allergy
Definition: A mollusc allergy triggered by snails.

Definition: A snail allergy triggered by Turbo cornutus.

Name: latex allergy
Definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by latex.

Name: hepatoid adenocarcinoma
Definition: An adenocarcinoma with morphologic characteristics similar to hepatocellular carcinoma, arising from an anatomic site other than the liver.

Name: Warsaw breakage syndrome
Definition: A syndrome mainly characterized by severe growth retardation and microcephaly. It is a new form of cohesinopathy showing defects in sister chromatid cohesion and hypersensitivity to chemicals that induce replication stress, thus combining distinct cytogenetic features seen in Roberts syndrome and Fanconi anemia, respectively. It is caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DDX11 gene on chromosome 12p11.

Name: mitochondrial complex I deficiency
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease characterized by a wide range of manifestations including marked and often fatal lactic acidosis, cardiomyopathy, leukoencephalopathy, pure myopathy and hepatopathy with tubulopathy. Among the numerous clinical phenotypes observed are Leigh syndrome, Leber hereditary optic neuropathy and MELAS syndrome. It can be caused by mutations in multiple different genes, both nuclear-encoded and mitochondrial-encoded.

Name: mitochondrial complex II deficiency
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease characerized by a highly variable phenotype. Some patients have multisystem involvement of the brain, heart, muscle, liver, and kidneys resulting in death in infancy, whereas others have only isolated cardiac or muscle involvement with onset in adulthood and normal cognition. It s caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the nuclear-encoded SDHA gene on chromosome 5p, the nuclear-encoded SDHAF1 gene on chromosome 19q, or the nuclear-encoded SDHD gene on chromosome 11q23.

Name: purpura fulminans
Definition: A purpura characterized blood spots, bruising and discolouration of the skin resulting from coagulation in small blood vessels within the skin and rapidly leads to skin necrosis and disseminated intravascular coagulation. It is often fatal.

Name: neoplastic disease
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in an abnormal mass of tissue.

Name: blastoma
Definition: A cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derived_from precursor cells called blast cells.

Name: myeloma
Definition: A bone marrow cancer that affects plasma cells in which abnormal plasma cells multiply uncontrollably in the bone marrow and occasionally in other parts of the body.

Name: muscular disease
Definition: A musculoskeletal system disease that affects the muscles.

Name: bone disease
Definition: A connective tissue disease that affects the structure or development of bone or causes an impairment of normal bone function.

Name: bone remodeling disease
Definition: A bone disease that results_in formation or resorption abnormalities located_in bone.

Name: bone development disease
Definition: A bone disease that results_in abnormal growth and development located_in bone or located_in cartilage.

Definition: A bone structure disease that results_in change or damage of structure located_in bone.

Definition: A bone disease that results_in an interruption of blood supply located_in bone.

Definition: A bone disease that has_material_basis_in an abnormality in the location or function of the skeletal structure.

Name: bone resorption disease
Definition: A bone remodeling disease that results in an abnormal decrease of bone density or mass.

Definition: A genetic disease that has_material_basis_in extra, missing, or re-arranged chromosomes.

Definition: A disease that has_material_basis_in a genetic abnormality, error with embryonic development, infection or compromised intrauterine environment.

Name: dysbaric osteonecrosis
Definition: An ischemic bone disease the has_material_basis_in nitrogen embolization located_in bone.

Name: metaphyseal dysplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that results_in thinning and the tendency to fracture located_in bone.

Definition: A metaphyseal dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in PTH receptor which results_in short-limbed dwarfism.

Name: Schmid metaphyseal chondrodysplasia
Definition: A metaphyseal dysplasia that results_in dwarfism and bowed legs.

Name: McKusick type metaphyseal dysplasia
Definition: A metaphyseal dysplasia that results_in short-limbed dwarfism and fine sparse hair.

Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that results from mutations in the COL11A2 gene which results_in enlargement of the located_in epiphysis in located_in hand and located_in foot, distinct facial features, platyspondyly and hearing loss.

Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that results_in abnormalities of bone growth located_in vertebral column, located_in epiphysis, located_in metaphysis.

Name: spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia, Missouri type
Definition: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the MMP13 gene which results_in a pear-shaped vertebrae, abnormal metaphyseal changes, and genu varum deformities.

Name: fibrous dysplasia
Definition: A bone remodeling disease that results_in the destruction of normal bone and replacing it with fibrous bone tissue.

Name: craniodiaphyseal dysplasia
Definition: An osteosclerosis that results_in increased calcium concentration located_in skull which decreases the size of cranium foramina and cervical spinal canal.

Name: craniometaphyseal dysplasia
Definition: An osteosclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutations in the ANKH gene which results_in progressive thickening located_in skull and abnormally shaped ends of long bones in the limbs.

Name: endosteal hyperostosis
Definition: A hyperostosis of endosteal bone.

Name: SOST-related sclerosing bone dysplasia
Definition: A hyperostosis that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the SOST gene which results_in overgrowth of endosteal bone producing dense and wide bones throughout the body especially located_in skull.

Name: Worth's syndrome
Definition: A hyperostosis that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the LRP5 gene which results_in increased bone density and bony structures located_in palate.

Name: pycnodysostosis
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the CTSK gene which results_in dwarfism, brittle bones, osteopetrosis, shortening of the distal phalanges.

Name: axial osteomalacia
Definition: An osteosclerosis that results_in coarsening located_in trabecular bone.

Name: fibrogenesis imperfecta ossium
Definition: A syndrome that involves abnormality of collagen synthesis in lamellar bones, with manifestations limited to the skeleton. The initial symptom is frequently spontaneous fractures.

Name: hypochondroplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FGFR3 gene which affects ossification of cartilage and results_in short limb dwarfism.

Name: achondrogenesis
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in deficient endochondral ossification which results_in dwarfism, short-trunk, short-limbed, anascara, disaprportionately large cranium, and a narrow chest which leads to death in utero or during early neonatal period.

Name: hypochondrogenesis
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the COL2A1 gene which affects bone growth and results_in a small body, hydrops fetalis, and abnormal ossification located_in vertebral column or located_in pelvis. The disease has_symptom enlarged abdomen.

Name: Kniest dysplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the COL2A1 gene which results_in dwarfism with a short trunk and limbs as well as vision and hearing problems. The disease has_symptom large joints, has_symptom wide set eyes, has_symptom round flat face.

Name: pseudoachondroplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the COMP gene which results_in short limb dwarfism.

Name: trichorhinophalangeal syndrome I
Definition: A

Name: acromesomelic dysplasia
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mesomelia and acromelia, which results_in short limb Dwarfism.

Name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Maroteaux type
Definition: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in NPR-B receptor which results_in severe dwarfism, abnormalities of the located_in vertebral column and shortening of middle and distal segments in the located_in limb.

Name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Hunter-Thompson type
Definition: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in AMDH gene which results_in normal axial skeleton but fused bones in the located_in hand or located_in foot.

Name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Grebe type
Definition: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in CDMP-1 which results_in micromelia, absence of middle and proximal phalanges and some metacarpal and metatarsal bones.

Name: Albright's hereditary osteodystrophy
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in lack of responsiveness to parathyroid hormone which results_in shortening and widening of long bones of the located_in hand or located_in foot along with short stature, obesity, and rounded face.

Name: achondrogenesis type IA
Definition: An achondrogenesis that results_in abnormal ossification of the located_in vertebral column or located_in spine.

Name: achondrogenesis type IB
Definition: An achondrogenesis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC26A2 gene which results_in umbilical or inguinal hernia and a prominent rounded abdomen.

Name: achondrogenesis type II
Definition: An achondrogenesis that has_material_basis_in mutations in the COL2A1 gene which results_in underdeveloped lungs, hydrops fetalis, a prominent forehead and abnormal ossification of the located_in vertebral column or located_in pelvis.

Name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 5
Definition: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized by pyramidal features including extensor plantar responses, mild increase in tone, and preserved or increased reflexes but no spastic gait.
Synonym: hereditary motor and sensory neuropathy with pyramidal features

Name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 6
Definition: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized by early-onset optic atrophy resulting in progressive visual loss and peripheral axonal sensorimotor neuropathy with highly variable age at onset and severity.
Synonym: hereditary motor and sensory neuropathy type 6

Name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 7
Definition: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized optic atrophy followed by retinitis pigmentosa.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 7
Synonym: alpha-b crystalin-related fatal infantile hypertonic myofibrillar myopathy

Name: myopathy, lactic acidosis, and sideroblastic anemia
microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 1
Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development and visual impairment, often accompanied by short stature and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the TUBGCP6 gene.

Name: microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 2
Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development, visual impairment, and short stature and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PLK4 gene.

Name: microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 3
Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by congenital microcephaly and chorioretinal dysplasia associated with poor vision and nystagmus and has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the TUBGCP4 gene.

Name: infantile myofibromatosis
Definition: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is characterized by the development of benign tumors in the skin, striated muscles, bones, and in exceptional cases, visceral organs.

Name: multiple pterygium syndrome
Definition: A genetic disease that is characterized by permanently bent fingers (camptodactyly), short stature, rocker-bottom or club feet, joints that are bent in a fixed position (contractures), union or webbing of the skin between the fingers (syndactyly), and/or webbing of the neck, inside bend of the elbows, back of the knees and armpits.

Name: intestinal infectious disease
Definition: An intestinal disease that involves intestinal infection caused by viruses, bacteria, fungi and parasites.

Name: visual cortex disorder due to neoplasm
respiratory syncytial virus bronchiolitis
Definition: A respiratory syncytial virus infectious disease that results_in inflammation located_in bronchiole, has_material_basis_in Human respiratory syncytial virus, which is transmitted_by droplet spread of nasal secretions from an infected person while coughing or sneezing, or transmitted_by contaminated fomites. Infection is characterized by inflammation, edema, and necrosis of the small airway epithelium with associated bronchospasm and increased mucous production.

Name: metastatic malignant neoplasm to the thyroid
Synonym: secondary malignant neoplasm of thyroid gland

Name: polyglandular activity in multiple endocrine adenomatosis
multiple endocrine neoplasia type 2B
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by medullary thyroid carcinoma, pheochromocytoma, multiple mucosal neuromas and intestinal ganglioneuromas, and often a marfanoid habitus and other skeletal abnormalities.

Name: multiple endocrine neoplasia type 1
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the MEN1 tumor suppressor gene and is characterized by over active endocrine glands frequently involving tumors of the parathyroid glands, the pituitary gland, and the pancreas.

Name: papilledema associated with increased intracranial pressure
ampulla of Vater cancer
Synonym: malignant tumour of ampulla of vater

Name: duodenum cancer
Definition: A small intestine cancer that is located_in the beginning section of the small intestine.

Name: ampulla of vater neoplasm
Synonym: tumor of the ampulla of vater

Definition: A migraine characterized by migraine headache which is preceded or accompanied by a transient focal neurological phenomenon.

The infection has_symptom intense, stabbing pain in the back and legs that recurs irregularly, has_symptom gait ataxia, has_symptom hyperesthesia, has_symptom paresthesia, has_symptom loss of bladder sensation leading to urine retention, has_symptom erectile dysfunction.

Name: asymptomatic neurosyphilis
Definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that results_in mild meningitis.

Name: old burn scar-related melanoma of skin
late congenital syphilis
Definition: A congenital syphilis that occurs in children at or greater than two years of age who acquired the infection trans-placentally. The infection has_symptom gummatous ulcers, has_symptom periosteal lesions, has_symptom paresis, has_symptom tabes, has_symptom optic atrophy, has_symptom interstitial keratitis, has_symptom sensorineural deafness, and has_symptom dental deformities.

Name: regressing skin melanoma
Synonym: regressing malignant melanoma of the skin

Name: malignant giant pigmented nevus melanoma
Synonym: skin melanoma in Giant Pigmented nevus

Name: nodular malignant melanoma
Definition: A melanoma that is characterized as highly aggressive and manifests as a uniform blue-black, blue-red, or amelanotic nodule.

Name: desmoplastic melanoma
Definition: A skin malanoma that results_in nonpigmented lesions located_in sun-exposed areas of the body, most commonly on the head and neck.

Name: Congenital or acquired abnormality of vagina complicating pregnancy, childbirth, or the puerperium
syphilitic acoustic neuritis
Definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that is caused due to syphilis, which occurs suddenly and produces tinnitus and deafness when the cochlear branch is affected whereas vertigo, disturbances of equilibrium, spontaneous nystagmus and vomiting when the vestibular branch suffers. A combination of these symptoms are seen when both the branches are involved.

Name: hymenolepiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the bowel by Hymenolepis nana or Hymenolepis diminuta. The symptoms include diarrhea, gastrointestinal discomfort, itchy anus, poor appetite and weakness.

Name: diphyllobothriasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection caused by Diphyllobothrium latum through the consumption of raw or undercooked fish. The symptoms include abdominal discomfort, diarrhea, vomiting, weight loss and vitamin B12 deficiency with pernicious anemia.

Name: cysticercosis
Definition: A taeniasis that results from ingestion of eggs or larvae of the Taenia solium tapeworm in undercooked pork or fecally contaminated food or water, which subsequently infect the central nervous system, heart, muscles, subcutaneous tissues, and eyes. Neurocysticercosis causes seizures, mental disturbances, focal neurologic deficits and intracerebral lesions.

Name: sparganosis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection by the genus Spirometra. A painful nodule develops after the plerocercoid larvae migrate to the brain causing cerebral sparganosis. Subcutaneous tissue, breast, orbit, urinary tract, pleural cavity, lungs, abdominal viscera and inner ear can be infected.

Name: Congenital or acquired abnormality of vagina, with delivery
sleeping sickness
Definition: A trypanosomiasis that results from infection by Trypanosoma brucei and gambiense, which is transmitted by the bite of an infected tsetse fly (Glossina spp). The symptoms include fever, headache, joint pain, itching, confusion, sensory disturbances, poor coordination and sleep disturbances.

Name: trypanosomiasis
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by parasitic protozoan of the genus Trypanosoma in animals and humans.

Name: Trypanosoma brucei rhodesiense infectious disease
Definition: A sleeping sickness that involves infection caused by Trypanosoma brucei rhodesiense, which is carried by the tsetse fly. The symptoms include fever, severe headache, irritability, extreme fatigue, swollen lymph nodes, aching muscles and joints, skin rash, progressive confusion, personality changes, and other neurologic problems.

Name: Trypanosoma brucei gambiense infectious disease
Definition: A sleeping sickness that involves infection caused by Trypanosoma brucei gambiense, which is carried by the tsetse fly. The symptoms include fever, rash, swelling of the face and hands, headaches, fatigue, aching muscles and joints, itching skin, swollen lymph nodes, progressive confusion, personality changes, daytime sleepiness with nighttime sleep disturbances, and other neurologic problems.

Name: degenerative disorder of eyelid and periocular area
keratoconus
Definition: A corneal disease characterized by structural changes within the cornea causing it to thin and change, leading to a protruding conical shape.

Name: venous insufficiency
Definition: A vein disease that is characterized by impaired flow of blood through the veins.

Name: Chlamydia trachomatis peritonitis
Synonym: venereal disease of peritoneum due to Chlamydia trachomatis

Name: secondary malignant neoplasm to the thymus
long bones of lower limb cancer

Synonym: malignant neoplasm of short bones of leg
